 The Boston Braves runner almost picked off first base in the 1948 World Series 
by Bob Feller of Cleveland was Phil (not Don) Masi. The Yankee pitcher in a 
later World Series whose bid for a no-hitter was spoiled with two outs in the 
ninth inning by the Brooklyn Dodgers Cookie Lavagetto's clutch hit was Bill 
Bevens (not Stevens). 
