<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: ORANGE COUNTY ALMANAC 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 "Red Hill" is the not-so-creative name for the rust-colored ridge of mercury 
ore near Browning Avenue and La Colina Drive in the north Tustin area. 
</P>
<P>
 The ancient landmark is also known as "Cerrito de las Ranas," or "Hill of the 
Frogs" -- a Spanish-language reference to the thousands of small green 
amphibians that once lived in a swampy area extending from the hill down to 
Newport Bay.The sound of croaking frogs could be heard for miles. 
</P>
<P>
 In the late 1800s and early 1900s, Red Hill was mined for its quicksilver. 
Today, it is surrounded by fashionable homes in an unincorporated area of 
Orange County. 
</P>
<P>
 Today 
</P>
<P>
 The Newport Harbor Area Chamber of Commerce will offer a "Business Start-Up 
</P>
<P>
 Checklist" workshop at 5:30 p.m. at the chamber's office. 
</P>
<P>
 The free seminar, which is open to all, will cover accounting, legal services, 
taxes and business planning. 
</P>
<P>
 After brief presentations from several speakers, participants will have a 
chance to ask questions. 
</P>
<P>
 The chamber office is at 1470 Jamboree Road. 
</P>
<P>
 Reservations: (714) 729-4400. 
</P>
</TEXT>
