 A computer record of Nasdaq trading in shares of Microsoft Inc. on Oct. 14 
shows that market makers reported nine trades out of sequence -- including two 
big ones for 50,000 shares each -- after the close of trading at 4 p.m. EDT 
(16:00 on the computer's big trades being reported just after the close 
