 Home Loan Program: The city of Los Angeles and the mortgage banking unit of 
Pittsburgh-based PNC Bank Corp. are set to announce a program Thursday aimed at 
overcoming traditional barriers to home ownership in South-Central Los Angeles: 
the lack of down payments and the inability to qualify for mortgages. PNC 
Mortgage, which plans to open an office in South-Central, will offer a new 
mortgage product for consumers who do not meet traditional credit requirements, 
as well as loans that require only a 3% down payment. 
