<TEXT>
<P>
 Economic Forecast Due: The first of the season's crop of 1995 economic outlook 
reports for Orange County will be delivered Friday at Cal State Fullerton by 
economics department Chairman Anil Puri. This is the third annual county 
forecast by the university's Institute for Economic and Environmental Studies 
and comes at a time when the signals are quite mixed.On the negative side, a 
long-awaited recovery is being threatened by a series of major plant closures 
and continued aerospace and computer industry layoffs. But state employment 
officials also say they underestimated job growth in California and that there 
may have been 200,000 more jobs created than originally thought. Against that 
backdrop, Puri will deliver his reading on the county's economic future, while 
First Interstate Bancorp economist Lynn Reaser will discuss the state and 
national forecasts. 
