<P>
 Whistle While You Watch: The videocassette version of Walt Disney's 1937 
classic, "Snow White and the Seven Dwarfs," which finally goes on sale this 
week, is expected to dwarf other video sales to date.The Burbank entertainment 
giant has confirmed that it has already received a record 27 million orders 
from retailers. Some are predicting that "Snow White" could become the first 
video to break the 30-million mark in units sold, besting the 24 million units 
of "Aladdin" that Disney sold and the 22 million units of "Beauty and the 
Beast." For Walt Disney Co., the video should fatten its pre-profits by more 
than $200 million. 
