between Adobe Systems Inc. and Aldus Corp., two computer graphics pioneers, 
settles charges that their merger could give them a lock on prices and reduce 
innovation. Adobe markets the Illustrator program and Aldus the Freehand 
program, both of which are used with Apple Computer's Macintosh and Power 
Macintosh computers. Under the deal, the merged firm will sell the Freehand 
software within six months to Altsys Corp., a software maker based in 
