<P>
 Insurer to Pay $200,000 Fine for Claims Delays: Philadelphia American Life 
Insurance Co., in a settlement of charges brought by the California Insurance 
Department, agreed to pay $200,000 and change its claims practices, the 
department announced Friday. Regulators last June had accused the company of 
225 cases in which it had either failed to acknowledge receipt of a claim or 
settle a claim within 15 days of its having been filed, as required by law. 
