<TEXT>
<P>
 Orange County Jobless Rates Rises: California's Employment Development 
Department reported that Orange County's unemployment rate edged up in 
September to 6%, from 5.9% in August, with several key sectors showing job 
losses.Overall, the county saw an expansion of 5,400 jobs last month from 
August, all of it seasonal, as an army of teachers and other school workers 
returned to their jobs. But a decline in payroll employment in manufacturing, 
retail trade, finance and real estate helped to lift up the county's jobless 
rate in September. The jobless rate increase contrasted with significant 
declines for the nation and the state. 
</P>
