</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By GREG HERNANDEZ 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Chamber of Commerce has hired a new executive director who will start work 
on Nov. 14. 
</P>
<P>
 Susan Klaren, 32, was chosen from a field of 40 candidates and replaces Alan 
Hughes, who worked as executive director for 11 years before stepping down in 
June. 
</P>
<P>
 Klaren was most recently the executive director of the West Suburban Chamber 
of Commerce in LaGrange, Ill., and has eight years of experience working with 
marketing and fund-raising for nonprofit organizations, said Jeff Farano, 
president of the Anaheim Chamber of Commerce. 
</P>
<P>
 "She had a lot of good ideas and appears to be able to follow through with 
them," Farano said.  
</P>
<P>
 Farano said one of Klaren's biggest challenges will be to attract more 
businesses to the city. 
</P>
<P>
 "We consider now a very crucial time with a lot going on," Farano said. "We're 
trying to get business back up again and we see the chamber playing a crucial 
role in the economic development of the city." 
</P>
<P>
 Klaren will be officially introduced to the business community at a reception 
on Nov. 16. GREG HERNANDEZ 
</P>
