COMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: MISSION VIEJO; PTA COUNCIL OPPOSES EL TORO BALLOT MEASURE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JEFF BEAN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Saddleback PTA Council has voted to oppose a ballot initiative calling for 
the conversion of the El Toro Marine Corps Air Station into a commercial 
airport. 
</P>
<P>
 The group represents PTA schools in Mission Viejo, Lake Forest, Laguna Hills, 
Foothill Ranch, Rancho Santa Margarita, Portola Hills and Trabuco Canyon. 
</P>
<P>
 The group said that the impact of building a commercial airport at the Marine 
Corps base has not been studied adequately, and that noise and pollution could 
affect nearby schools and children. 
</P>
<P>
 Supporters of the initiative, Measure A, say a commercial airport will create 
new jobs and provide an economic boost to the county. 
</P>
<P>
 The Capistrano PTA Council has also voted to oppose the ballot initiative. 
JEFF BEAN 
